description: Requires comprehensive migration
High semantic preservation across all agents
Major breaking reorganization
Loss of expectedOutput constraints
Balanced by high correctness and semantic preservation
AAVA 2.0 introduces breaking structural changes while preserving core agent semantics
Workflow identifier moved from root pipeline to workFlowDetail container
Pipeline container renamed to workFlowDetail with different structure
Agent container renamed from pipeLineAgents to workflowAgents
Agent renamed to DI Token Size Estimator S3 IMS HP with preserved semantic role
Agent renamed to DI Pagewise TML To CSV Converter S3 IMS HP with preserved semantic role
Agent renamed to DI ThoughtSpotSQL To Lvdashboard Converter S3 IMS HP with preserved semantic role
Agent renamed to DI PageWise ThoughtSpotSQL To Individual Lvdashboard Creator S3 IMS HP Clone with preserved semantic role
Agent renamed to DI Pagewise Thoughspot Json Merger S3 IMS HP Clone with preserved semantic role
Agent ID field renamed from id to agentId
Agent role field removed
Agent goal field removed
Agent backstory field removed
Task structure flattened into description field
Expected output specification removed
LLM configuration restructured into modelDeploymentName and agentDetails
Detailed tool definitions removed replaced with toolReferences
Verbose field moved to agentDetails
Allow delegation field moved to agentDetails
Max iterations field moved to agentDetails
Max execution time field moved to agentDetails
Temperature moved from llm to agentDetails
TopP moved from llm to agentDetails

Complete structural reorganization requires coordinated migration
